prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: The night of the abuse was scary. I had never seen that side of him before and it came out of nowhere. One minute we were sitting around laughing and the next I was up against the wall as I was being yelled at and spit on. Alcohol. Alcohol does this to people. People that you would least expect it to. I didn't even know my fiance was having any problems. He never told me of any emotional issues or issues at work that he was dealing with. That's the thing about men though, they bottle everything up inside of them because it's not "manly" to vent. We had never even had an argument. I didn't do or say anything to make him mad. It literally just happened in the blink of an eye. People that drink every day are covering up problems. It's not normal to come home and get drunk every night. This is the number one sign and I missed it. I should've seen that something was wrong and for that I partially blame myself.

choices.text: I was completely taken off guard and scared for my life. I didn't know what to do. He never hit me but he was very intimidating and I was scared to say anything. I just wanted to get out of there. I didn't even care if I had to sleep on the street that night. The worst part of it all is that he apologized the next day and acted like nothing was wrong. He said he didn't remember any of it and that he must have been having a bad dream. I knew that wasn't true but I played along because I didn't know what else to do. That was the beginning of the end of our relationship. I knew I couldn't trust him and that he had a dark side that I never knew existed.
